data.description: PRICE IMPROVEMENT! OPEN HOUSE SATURDAY 12-2PM. Discover a home where traditional elegance meets modern comfort in the desirable Powell Valley area of Gresham. This 2,370-square-foot, 2-story gem, built in 2007, is ideally positioned just a short distance from Historic Downtown Troutdale - The Gateway to the Gorge. Situated on a sprawling 5,836-square-foot lot on a quiet street off the main road, the property exudes curb appeal, with no HOA.Make this your home for the holidays and beyond! Dive into the spacious backyard that's bursting with potential. From garden parties to family barbecues, there's plenty of room to bring all your outdoor visions to life. The durable back deck is a summertime dream, where warm evenings can be spent enjoying the tranquility and making memories. Don't miss this opportunity to embrace a space that promises not only indoor comfort but also expansive outdoor delights.The home's location is second to none. Enjoy the convenience of being within walking distance to Powell Valley Elementary & Gordon Russell Middle School. It is also zoned for the sought-after Sam Barlow High School. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by hickory hardwood flooring connecting the main-level spaces, radiating warmth and sophistication.The home's layout features four spacious bedrooms and a bonus room. The primary suite upstairs is a haven, complete with its own ensuite bathroom. Additionally, a sizable bonus room upstairs offers versatile space for recreation, relaxation, or an additional office.The heart of the home, the kitchen, boasts newer Samsung appliances, ensuring your culinary endeavors are always a delight. This home includes a washer and dryer and a 3-car garage with 2 tandem spaces.Representing a perfect blend of quality, comfort, and modern living, this isn't just a move-in ready property - it's a residence you'd be elated to call home.
